comment_data.body: Thanks, this is definitely more correct place to resolve.

According to the screenshots, code highlighting works fine.
By default, classes do not have special highlighting. It's possible to install 3rd party plugins that add color themes to IntelliJ IDEA or to tune standard color scheme in Settings (Preferences) | Editor | Color Scheme | Dart.

Thanks @alexander-doroshko!  Any thoughts on the emphasis on **Scaffold** here?:

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/67586/51188067-0a620a80-1892-11e9-8ceb-d20c091d1c97.png)
@pq, see Settings (Preferences) | Editor | Color Scheme | Dart. By default, constructors have special highlighting in Darcula theme, but no special highlighting in Default (light) theme.

It will be great if you will add colorful syntax theme shown on Flutter Live '18 demos.
Newcomers expecting that.
Power saver mode will also have an impact File>Power Save Mode
